<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="449" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,565,2030]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,565,590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species comes close to 
<taxonomicName authority="van der Vecht, 1963" authorityName="van der Vecht" authorityYear="1963" box="[620,1114,565,590]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keiseri">
<emphasis box="[620,865,565,589]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Ectopioglossa keiseri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="van der Vecht, J." box="[875,1114,565,590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref15727" refString="van der Vecht, J. (1963) Studies on Indo-Australian and East Asiatic Eumenidae (Hymenoptera: Vespoidea). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden, 60, 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1963">van der Vecht, 1963</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gusenleitner, 1990" authorityName="Gusenleitner" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henseni">
<emphasis box="[1181,1435,565,589]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Ectopioglossa henseni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gusenleitner, J." box="[151,365,601,626]" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" pagination="571 - 575" refId="ref14794" refString="Gusenleitner, J. (1990) Eine neue Art der Gattung Ectopioglossa Perkins 1912 (Hymenoptera, Vespoidea, Eumenidae). Linzer biologische Beitrage, 22 (2), 571 - 575." type="journal article" year="1990">Gusenleitner, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the presence of an apical raised lamella on T3, which is absent in the other species of the genus. It can be recognized by [characteristics of the other two species in brackets]: punctures on pronotum indistinct and clearly smaller than those on mesoscutum [similar to those on mesoscutum in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gusenleitner" authorityYear="1990" box="[1197,1314,673,697]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henseni">
<emphasis box="[1197,1314,673,697]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. henseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and larger in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van der Vecht" authorityYear="1963" box="[180,287,709,733]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keiseri">
<emphasis box="[180,287,709,733]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. keiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
], lateral face of propodeum densely and finely striate and without punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1243,709,734]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–13" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[175,1436,437,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,437,1951]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 10–13. Ectopioglossa luzonica sp. nov., ♀, holotype. 10, Habitus. 11, Head in frontal view. 12, Metasoma in lateral view. 13, Propodeum in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3769480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3769480/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) [strongly striate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gusenleitner" authorityYear="1990" box="[182,301,745,769]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henseni">
<emphasis box="[182,301,745,769]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. henseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and with punctures in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van der Vecht" authorityYear="1963" box="[569,677,745,769]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keiseri">
<emphasis box="[569,677,745,769]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. keiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
], T1–T2 almost entirely impunctate [with distinct punctures in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gusenleitner" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henseni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. henseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van der Vecht" authorityYear="1963" box="[291,397,781,805]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keiseri">
<emphasis box="[291,397,781,805]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. keiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
], hairs on T3–T5 longer than height of apical lamella of T3 (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1164,781,806]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–13" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[175,1436,437,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,437,1951]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 10–13. Ectopioglossa luzonica sp. nov., ♀, holotype. 10, Habitus. 11, Head in frontal view. 12, Metasoma in lateral view. 13, Propodeum in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3769480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3769480/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) [shorter in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gusenleitner" authorityYear="1990" box="[1303,1419,781,805]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="henseni">
<emphasis box="[1303,1419,781,805]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. henseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
], legs black with yellow markings [ferrugineous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van der Vecht" authorityYear="1963" box="[705,810,817,841]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keiseri">
<emphasis box="[705,810,817,841]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. keiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
], wings with yellow tinge [strongly fuscous with purple reflections in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van der Vecht" authorityYear="1963" box="[305,410,853,877]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Ectopioglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keiseri">
<emphasis box="[305,410,853,877]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="449">E. keiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
